{"kind":"article","sections":[],"topicSectionsStyle":"detailedGrid","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In a recent Mission Dharma "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"http:\/\/www.missiondharma.org\/dharma-talks.html","type":"reference"},{"text":" Howie Cohn talked about winter. He mentioned plants going dormant and wildlife hibernating. He emphasized that this is the season for rest.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"I’d never thought of winter this way. I’d been irritated by the short days and long nights. I’d been sad when the skies were gray for weeks at a time."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"But the perspective Howie shared makes complete sense. I was trying to live in a way that was not in accord with the season — I was trying to fight nature and therefore I was suffering.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I know to embrace this season of rest."}]}]}],"metadata":{"platforms":[{"name":"Brunow","introducedAt":"2016.01.02"}],"color":{"standardColorIdentifier":"purple"},"modules":[{"name":"Brunow"}],"title":"The Winter Season"},"abstract":[{"text":"Winter is for rest.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/brunow\/01-02-the-winter-season"]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/01-02-the-winter-season","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow","doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/Archive","doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/2016"]]},"references":{"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow/2016":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/2016","url":"\/documentation\/brunow\/2016","abstract":[],"role":"collectionGroup","title":"2016"},"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow/Archive":{"url":"\/documentation\/brunow\/archive","title":"Archive","role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"All posts"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/Archive","kind":"article"},"http://www.missiondharma.org/dharma-talks.html":{"identifier":"http:\/\/www.missiondharma.org\/dharma-talks.html","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Dharma Talk","type":"text"}],"title":"Dharma Talk","url":"http:\/\/www.missiondharma.org\/dharma-talks.html","type":"link"},"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/brunow","title":"Brunow","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"David Brunow, known as Brunow [ˈbɹunoʊ] to the folks he works with, is a human living on Earth. You might have something in common with him — if you think it is ridiculous that he is talking about himself in the first person here, so does he.","type":"text"}],"role":"collection"}}}